        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued August 1 at 2:57PM EDT until August 1 at 4:00PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>SVRGSP

The National Weather Service in Greenville-Spartanburg has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
East central Rutherford County in western North Carolina...
Northwestern Cleveland County in the Piedmont of North Carolina...

* Until 400 PM EDT.

* At 257 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 14 miles northeast
of Forest City, or 4 miles southwest of Casar, moving southeast at
10 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to trees and power lines.

* Locations impacted include...
Polkville and Casar.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.

Please report damaging winds, hail, or flooding to the National
Weather Service by calling toll free, 1, 800, 2 6 7, 8 1 0 1, or by
posting on our Facebook page, or post it to X using hashtag nwsgsp.
Your message should describe the event and the specific location
where it occurred.</instruction>
